"Yadav R.R.","Tree ring evidence of a 20th century precipitation surge in the monsoon shadow zone of the western Himalaya, India",2011,"Journal of Geophysical Research Atmospheres","116","2", D02112,"","",,,10.1029/2010JD014647,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79251636530&partnerID=40&md5=b9952c1eb39d90fa936157a058fd79a0","Birbal Sahni Institute of Palaeobotany, 53 University Rd., Lucknow 226007, India","Yadav, R.R., Birbal Sahni Institute of Palaeobotany, 53 University Rd., Lucknow 226007, India","The present study is the first attempt to develop an annual (August-July) precipitation series back to AD 1330 using a tree ring data network of Himalayan cedar (Cedrus deodara (Roxb.) G. Don) from the Lahaul-Spiti region in the western Himalaya, India. The rainfall reconstruction reveals high magnitude multidecadal droughts during the 14th and 15th centuries and thenceforth a gradual increase in precipitation. Increasingly wet conditions during the 20th century are consistent with other long-term precipitation reconstructions from high Asia and reflect a large-scale intensification of the hydrological cycle, coincident with what is anticipated due to global warming. Significant relationships between reconstructed precipitation and precipitation records from central southwest Asia, east of the Caspian Sea, ENSO (NINO4-SST) variability and summer monsoon rainfall over central northeast India underscore the utility of our data in synoptic climatology. Copyright 2011 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Atmospheric thermodynamics; Climatology; Global warming; Rain; 15th century; 20th century; Caspian sea; Himalayas; Hydrological cycles; Precipitation reconstruction; Shadow zone; Summer monsoon rainfall; Synoptic climatology; Tree ring data; Tree rings; Wet conditions; Trees (mathematics); coniferous tree; drought; El Nino-Southern Oscillation; global warming; paleoclimate; precipitation intensity; rainfall; tree ring; twentieth century; Caspian Sea; Himalayas; India; Cedrus deodara",,,,,,"Anderson, D.M., Overpeck, J.T., Gupta, A.K., Increase in the Asian southwest monsoon during the past four centuries (2002) Science, 297 (5581), pp. 596-599. , DOI 10.1126/science.1072881; Archer, D.R., Fowler, H.J., Spatial and temporal variations in precipitation in the upper Indus basin, global teleconnections and hydrological implications (2004) Hydrol. Earth Syst. Sci., 8, pp. 47-61. , doi:10.5194/hess-8-47-2004; Bhutiyani, M.R., Kale, V.S., Pawar, N.J., Climate change and the precipitation variations in the northwestern Himalaya: 1886-2006 (2009) Int. J. Climatol., 30, pp. 535-548. , doi:10.1002/joc.1920; Blanford, H.F.L., On the connexion of Himalayan snowfall and seasons of drought in India (1884) Proc. R. Soc. London, 37, pp. 3-22. , doi:10.1098/ rspl.1884.0003; Briffa, K.R., Jones, P.D., Bartholin, T.S., Eckstein, D., Schweingruber, F.H., Karlen, W., Zetterberg, P., Eronen, M., Fennoscandian summers from AD 500: Temperature changes on short and long timescales (1992) Clim. Dyn., 7, pp. 111-119. , doi:10.1007/BF00211153; Cobb, K.M., Charles, C.D., Cheng, H., Edwards, R.L., El Nino/ Southern Oscillation and tropical Pacific climate during the last millennium (2003) Science, 424, pp. 271-276; Cook, E.R., (1985) A Time Series Approach to Tree-Ring Standardization, , Ph.D. thesis Univ. of Ariz., Tucson; Cook, E.R., Peters, K., Calculating unbiased tree-ring indices for the study of climatic and environmental change (1997) Holocene, 7, pp. 361-370. , doi:10.1177/095968369700700314; Cook, E.R., Meko, D.M., Stahle, D.W., Cleaveland, M.K., Drought reconstruction for the continental United States (1999) J. Clim., 12, pp. 1145-1162. , doi:10.1175/1520-0442(1999)0121145:DRFTCU2.0.CO;2; Cook, E.R., Buckley, B.M., D'Arrigo, R., Peterson, M.J., Warm-season temperature since 1600 BC reconstructed from Tasmanian tree rings and their relationship to large-scale sea surface temperature anomalies (2000) Clim. Dyn., 16, pp. 79-91. , doi:10.100